In this file I just write all the comments which I will discover in my journey.

1. Initialize new git repo in your current directory 	-->	git init

2. Copies a repository from a remote source to your local machine.	-->	git clone <repo_url>

3. Stages changes from commit	-->	git add <file_name>
   To add all changes	-->	git add .

4.Records the changes made to the repository.	-->	git commit -m 'commit message'

5. Show the status of changes as untracked, modified, or staged.	-->	git status

6. Fetches changes from a remote repository and merges them into the current branch.	-->	git pull

7.
